<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The visibility of the member variable _memcache - which is the real/raw memcache object - is set to private. This disables the possibility to extend the class and use the memcache object. In my case I wanted to add functions like in- decrement functions but had to change the visibility in order to allow access to the object.</p>

<p>Interesting question is - maybe should be a new issue. Is it possible to add support for the in- decrement memcache calls.</p>

